==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[aequilibrium]]'', from ''[[aequus]]'', equal, and ''[[libra]]'', balance

===Noun===
'''equilibrium''' (''plural'' '''[[equilibria]]''')
#The [[condition]] of a [[system]] in which [[competing]] [[influence]]s are [[balance]]d.
#{{physics}} The state of a [[body]] at [[rest]] or in [[uniform]] [[motion]] in which the [[resultant]] of all [[force]]s on it is [[zero]].
#{{chemistry}} The state of a [[reaction]] in which the [[rate]]s of the [[forward]] and [[reverse]] reactions are the same.
#[[Mental]] balance.

====Derived terms====
*[[disequilibrium]]
